<paragraph blockId="16.[151,531,1466,1493]" box="[151,531,1466,1493]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,531,1466,1493]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,531,1466,1493]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">
<taxonomicName box="[151,355,1466,1492]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="veraepacis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,355,1466,1492]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">Sorex veraepacis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1537,1706]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[201,391,1538,1561]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="veraepacis">
<emphasis box="[201,391,1538,1561]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">Sorex veraepacis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group can be distinguished from other members of 
<taxonomicName box="[1057,1119,1538,1561]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1057,1119,1538,1561]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">Sorex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in NCA by not possessing a postmandibular foramen and canal, U3 is usually shorter than U4, and younger individuals have a pigmented ridge on the lingual side of the unicuspid teeth. Their color is gray to dark gray or black often with white tips on guard hairs. The species group contains four species: composed of 
<taxonomicName box="[844,991,1645,1670]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chiapensis">
<emphasis box="[844,991,1645,1670]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">S. chiapensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1007,1115,1645,1670]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ibarrai">
<emphasis box="[1007,1115,1645,1670]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">S. ibarrai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1131,1282,1646,1669]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="veraepacis">
<emphasis box="[1131,1282,1646,1669]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">S. veraepacis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the new species from the Sierra Madre of southwestern Guatemala.
</paragraph>
